	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jan 4th 10:45 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Intro:<br>==================================================<br>Ok here's some stuff I like to do. First off you need to recognize what class you will be dueling, and set up your spells accordingly, since we are enchanters, we have the advantage of time, on our hands. <br>==================================================<br>Dueling Casters:<br>Well, for enchanters to duel other casters, a lot of the time if you know what you're doing casters can be the easiest classes to duel. <br><br>Spells to have up:<br>Mana seive<br>Tashani<br>2 color stun spells<br>2 nukes<br>Mez<br>whatever else you want i'm not sure how many slots are in spells right now so whatever.<br><br><br>As soon as he hits duel, you want to stun the poor caster, tashani, stun again, then mez. <br>When he is mezzed I would cast Mana seive at least 5 times on him, this will drain a lot of his mana, but it does cost a lot of mana to you also. Good thing this is a non damage spell so it will not break mez. You can keep him mezzed, and regain mana. When he is manaless a.k.a. useless. Nuke the sucker to death. Nuff said.<br><br>Put it this way in duels, you want to think, what is this classes greatest strength? You, as an enchanter, have the ability to take away his greatest strengths. And this is what makes enchanters the greatest duelers. <br>==================================================<br>Dueling Melee:<br>Enchanters and melee, they are easy as well, except for the case of the bard who has awesome MR songs.&nbsp;&nbsp;Nearly all of our spells are magic based so when it comes to bards I am open for plenty of tips.<br><br>Spells to have:<br><br>Mez<br>2 Color stuns<br>Tashan (Tashani Tashania)<br>2 stackable strength debuffs<br>Nuke<br>Slow spell<br><br>Melee has accepted the battle to fight...<br><br>First thing you want to do if you are up close and personal is stun him.  Then Mez him.  Get as far away from him as you can while still being able to go in casting range.  Tashan first, then lay down your strength debuffs on him.  (Our strength line of debuffs makes for the best snares in the game PVP wise, it lasts way longer then root and that's exactly what it will do, it will make them so encumbered that they can't move)<br>Slow him, just in case if the strength wares off and he comes up close you will still have the advantage of stunning while he is slowed, it will make things easier.  Now med up until Full mana, and nuke the sucker to death...nuff said.  For those of you who think enchanters aren't the best in dueling, we are.  And this is exactly why.  <br><br><br>Hope this was of some use to you all<br><br>By the way I post on my guilds website, strategies, creation, all that nice stuff you can check out our website and my postings at www.webgenieus.net/arias<br>go under forums and mystical arts division<br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Damaddil&lt;Arias'tama&gt;<br>57 Beguiler<br><br>Rizen&lt;Arias'tama&gt;<br>36 Bard<br><br>Fennin Ro</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
